<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/9–1444: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                                <persName>Myron C. Taylor</persName>, Personal Representative of
                            President <persName>Roosevelt</persName> to <persName type="to">Pope
                                Pius XII</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-14T19:00:00-04:00">September 14,
                                1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>32. We feel it is premature to inform the Pope of the trend of discussions
                        and drafting now going on concerning the International Organization. At a
                        later stage I hope to be able to send you some useful background information
                        concerning recent developments which can be given to the Pope.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>